            NAME            NAME
            make.box - Draws a box on the map.
            
            SYNOPSIS            SYNOPSIS
            make.box [filename]            make.box                                 ________ 
            
            DESCRIPTION            DESCRIPTION
            make.box constructs a box, much the same as the            ________                                       
            make.neatline command, at a defined location on the map            _____________                                          
            composition.  The location for the box may be identified on
            the screen or through centimeter coordinates.  If given,
            [filename] is used for the name of the overlay file             ________                                          
            generated.  Multiple files may be generated for the map
            composition by using unique overlay file names.
            
            The user is required to provide the following:
            
                 - map definition file name
                 - an overlay file name (if not specified on the command
                      line)
                 - relationship of the box to a window
                      within the map composition
                 - plotter pen number
                 - location (see getting map location) of the box
            
            Completing the response sequence generates the required
            files to construct the map element.  Definition parameters
            are stored in the misc directory; graphic elements to draw                              ____                                    
            the map on the screen or plotter are stored in the ovm                                                               ___
            directory.  The default file name for both directories is
            box.            ____
            
            Changing the appearance of the box (e.g. position, size,
            etc.) can be done by regenerating the make.box command and                                                  ________            
            overwriting the initial file, or by editing the text
            definition file, then executing it directly, or by using the
            redo.misc command.            _________         
            
                 (edit) example:          vi misc/[filename]                                                   ________ 
                                          vi misc/box                                             ________
            
            Information entered through the interactive make.box command                                                        ________        
            has been reformatted to meet the requirements of the MAPGEN
            command legend, prefacing the element characteristics with                    ______                                            
            options for the legend command.  All options available in                            ______                                   
            the legend command are available for use in the GRASS-MAPGEN                ______                                                  
            Interface.  Commonly used legend options associated with                                      ______                        

